abstract: >-
  Reference governance patterns, schemas, and runnable implementations
  for audit-ready autonomous AI agents in regulated financial services.
  Covers autonomy-level classification (A0 through A4) — a proprietary
  governance framework documented in this repository — along with
  DEFCON-style risk-state degradation, sovereign veto architecture,
  shadow-mode rollout, tamper-evident hash-chain audit logging, and
  EU AI Act control mapping. Patterns were extracted from a multi-year
  autonomous trading system build, drawing on hundreds of engineering
  sessions, architectural decision records, and documented failure-mode
  analyses. The source system operates in paper-trading Phase 0 —
  no live capital has been deployed.
